The paper deals with the k-server problem, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses lower bounds and competitive algorithms, which are topics in computational complexity (cs.CC) and game theory (cs.GT), respectively. The paper also introduces new algorithms that require advice, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper deals with sparse graphs and treewidth, which are topics in graph theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG).
